# Page Section Debug IDs

When adding a new component to a page or introducing a new key section in a page/layout, the outermost container for that unit must include a unique `id` for easier debugging and DOM inspection.

## Required implementation

- Add an `id` on the top-level container of each newly added page-level component or key section.
- Ensure each `id` is unique within the page.
- Use stable, descriptive kebab-case names that reflect page and section purpose.
- Prefer semantic wrappers (`section`, `main`, `aside`, `header`) when possible, with the `id` on that outer wrapper.
- Keep existing IDs intact unless there is a direct conflict.

## Naming guidance

- Format: `<page>-<section>-<purpose>`
- Good examples: `website-domains-overview`, `permissions-role-table`, `appshell-primary-nav`
- Avoid generic IDs like `container`, `wrapper`, or `section1`

## Example pattern

```jsx
export function WebsitePage() {
  return (
    <main id="website-main-content">
      <section id="website-connected-domains">
        <ConnectedDomains />
      </section>

      <section id="website-dns-records">
        <DnsRecords />
      </section>
    </main>
  );
}
```
